Beethoven breathe life into such unwieldy form and make the bearer the highest thoughts presenting Bachs fugues among the greatest contrapuntal works Peter Kivy points out that counterpoint itself since time out mind has been associated the thinking musicians with the profound and the serious and argues that there seems some rational justification for their doing This related the idea that restrictions create freedom for the composer directing their efforts also points out that fugal writing has its roots improvisation and was during the Renaissance practiced improvisatory art Writing 1555 Nicola Vicentino for example suggests that the composer having completed the initial imitative entrances take the passage which has served accompaniment the theme and make the basis for new imitative treatment that will always have material with which compose without having stop and reflect This formulation the basic rule for fugal improvisation anticipates later sixteenthcentury discussions which deal with the improvisational technique the keyboard more extensively 